<tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/9/00 8:50:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards role in Plane of Fear</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't worry too much about lure.  I dont even use it in fear.  I just load up a couple draughts and stuns blast depending on which mob im fighting.<br><br>Scarelings - stun spells (not interupts since its a proc)<br>Dispelling mobs - stun spells (see above)<br><br>Everything else i use a draught against.  Some mobs seem more resistant to some types so I tend to use a couple damage types.  I couldn't comment on what resists what cause my memory is bad.<br><br>If exp is your goal then use IC cause then you can KS.  But when you're in the planes its stupid to worry about exp so Id suggest being efficient.<br><br>If your guild is pretty good at constant pulls then Id suggest working on the top half of your mana bar.  Try to maintain 70% mana on the off chance that a bad pull happens.  Then when the shit hits the fan you can run up into melee combat and rip to shreads some mobs quickly to help get the situation under control.  Just make sure you dont get yurself killed.<br><br>If your guild is inconsistant in their pulls hten I'd suggest opening up and hovering around 20% mana.  Odds are by the next pull you'll be FOM anywyas. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/9/00 8:55:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards role in Plane of Fear</span><hr size=1> If you have 3+ wizards all hovering around 70% mana and a bad pull happens the wizards can quickly get things under control.  Ive seen disasterous pulls happen where the 'chanters all died on impact.  Since the wizards were all conservative upto this point we all jump into melee combat (so we dont start ping ponging) and rip to shreads mob after mob with draughts.  Its amazing how fast 3 wizards can tear down a mob when they have a full mana bar <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Problem usually is that wizards know they can KS, so they play this little game where they get enough mana to KS and then empty their bar on one mob to ensure the kill.  I've been there and done it too so Im not gonna say shame on you all for doing it.  Im just saying that if you want to maximize yourself for the guild's benefit than ignore the exp and concentrate on taking down the mobs that you're most needed for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unedturbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nedtur Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/16/00 10:12:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards role in Plane of Fear</span><hr size=1> Well mate if you wanna be pretty sure to get your spells to hit,Then go to Melee range and just fire off your Ice Comet. Butbe sure to not nuke to much /em died way to many times like that=)<br><br>If you want exp up there. <br><br>The killing blowis what really counts. Just plan your nukes with the rest offyour group and power nuke from 30-40% Hp. Just fire off as manyIC as you can when they are at 40 so you really get up the agrolist that way you will have a better chance off gettin exp<br><br>Nedtur Mini´Mazurka <br>Best Dancer on Brell =)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulamrossthewicked.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lamross the Wicked</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/neonihilism/icon.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/17/00 1:59:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/neonihilism/lamrossicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards role in Plane of Fear</span><hr size=1> Hey Bael,<br><br>I was wondering where you went.<br><br>I've grouped with Neuro, Bazazu, and Ang in PoF and found the strategy of the &quot;Nuke Group&quot; to be the best role for wizards (and bards).<br><br>Get 3 wizards, 1 bard, and 2 druids in one group.  One wizard calls for an IC at roughly 60-80% health, which is immediately followed by a draught.<br><br>This is a LOT of damage in basically 10 seconds, its  KS method, but it helps in preperation of Dragons and such since you'll need to pulse nuke instead of overburn-chain nuking when it comes to wizards.<br><br>I dont see how this deals with quests, but wth... I'll respond.<br><br>lol<br><br>btw Bael.. I did my first hate raid today as a wizard, it was fun.. since they changed the taunt on 50+ warriors, its hard to KS now, so the nuke group isnt garunteed all the xp anymore.<br><br> <p><center><img src= "http://www.geocities.com/neonihilism/mannarobe.jpg"><br><b> Lamross Airporter</b><br><i> 46th Level Wizard of Morell-Thule<br><font size="2">Roombomber, Quad-kiter, and all around bad-ass!</font></i></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=71.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=71.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=71.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.threadControl?topicID=71.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=71.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=71.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpa